                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d895">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.248/581: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-18T14:00:00+03:00"
                            >June 18, 1942—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8:56 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>625. My 607, June 15. Turkish military authorities yesterday proposed to Colonel
                    Jadwin that our officers give their parole. I have advised Colonel Jadwin to
                    inform Turkish authorities that no reply will be made to their proposal until
                    instructions have been received by Embassy from Washington.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
